{
  "texts": [
    "Net.Visual Geometry Group (VGG) is a complex CNN architecture that is typical and contains numerous layers.",
    "In 2014, scientists from the University of Oxford, Karen Simonyan and Andrew Zisserman, presented the VGGNet framework for CNNs [100].",
    "The term \"deep\" refers to the number of layers, with VGG-16 or VGG-19 having 16 and 19 neural network layers, respectively.",
    "VGG architecture operates as the footing for innovative visual recognition techniques.",
    "The VGGNet, designed as a deep neural network, outperforms benchmarks on many tasks and databases outside ImageNet."
  ]
}